Nothing was so common, amidst the festivals of all ancient nations, as the introduction of wreaths or garlands of flowers. In the nuptial ceremonies of the Hebrews, the bridegroom was always encircled with a costly ornament of this kind, which is the decora* tion referred to by Isaiah in cap. lxi. 10. and in some readings, is literally so rendered. It is also more clearly designated in various places of the Psalms, and especially in the Song of Songs. But, at other feasts, as well as at the bridal banquet‚ a similar chaplet was introduced : thus, in Lamentations‚ cap. v. 15.
